{"id":25121346193,"name":"Test","node_id":"WFR_kwLOA_1uaM8AAAAF2VlSkQ","head_branch":"feat/security-csp","head_sha":"d2b6a4b1992f92fcdd94fe07012aab0e7f41f8bc","path":".github/workflows/run-tests.yml","run_number":53029,"run_attempt":1,"event":"pull_request","display_title":"feat: centralize CSP handling with marker annotations","status":"completed","conclusion":"failure","workflow_id":10954,"check_suite_id":66745472828,"check_suite_node_id":"CS_kwDOA_1uaM8AAAAPilcXPA","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/25121346193","html_url":"https://github.com/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/25121346193","pull_requests":[{"id":3591007391,"number":23753,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/pulls/23753","head":{"ref":"feat/security-csp","sha":"d2b6a4b1992f92fcdd94fe07012aab0e7f41f8bc","repo":{"id":66940520,"name":"dhis2-core","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core"}},"base":{"ref":"master","sha":"425548bc05cbbc8535c25b585d7a227c1a933602","repo":{"id":66940520,"name":"dhis2-core","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core"}}}],"created_at":"2026-04-29T16:35:26Z","updated_at":"2026-04-29T16:51:20Z","run_started_at":"2026-04-29T16:35:26Z","jobs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/25121346193/jobs","logs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/25121346193/logs","check_suite_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/check-suites/66745472828","artifacts_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/25121346193/artifacts","cancel_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/25121346193/cancel","rerun_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/25121346193/rerun","head_commit":{"message":"feat: centralize CSP handling with marker annotations and baseline filter\n\nReplace the legacy CspFilter + ad-hoc HeaderUtils.setSecurityHeaders calls\nwith a single CspInterceptor backed by CspPolicyService. The CSP policy is\nresolved from semantic marker annotations on controller handlers:\n\n- (no annotation) -\u003e default CSP\n- @CspUserUploadedContent -\u003e strict default-src 'none' for user-uploaded files\n- @CspAppHost -\u003e app-host policy for the AppController iframe shell\n- @CspLegacyLoginFallback -\u003e script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' for /login.html\n\nCspBaselineFilter (OncePerRequestFilter) emits the default CSP plus\nX-Content-Type-Options and X-Frame-Options on every response so 404s,\nstatic-resource handlers and pre-DispatcherServlet rejections still carry\nsecurity headers. CspInterceptor overrides CSP for handler-mapped requests\nvia setHeader, so annotation-driven policies win.\n\nAll CSP rule strings live in CspConstants. Annotations are zero-parameter\nmarkers so the rule set is auditable in one place; controllers carry only\nintent.\n\n@CspUserUploadedContent applied to file/document/audit/data-value/icon/\nmessage-attachment endpoints and to all eight tracker file/image endpoints\nthat previously inherited CSP headers from RequestHandler.serve.\n\nRemoves the legacy CspFilter, HeaderUtils, and CspFilterTest. The CORS\ndata path migration (which CspPolicyService depends on) ships in the\nprerequisite PR feat/security-cors-systemsettings.\n\nAdds unit tests for CspInterceptor and CspPolicyService and an E2E suite\n(CspHeadersE2ETest, CorsWhitelistE2ETest) that asserts headers land on\nreal responses.\n\nAI Assisted","author":{"name":"Morten Svanaes","email":"msvanaes@dhis2.org"},"id":"d2b6a4b1992f92fcdd94fe07012aab0e7f41f8bc","tree_id":"b319778a9bf80b3bc6cea29d5c222d56fcdc06fe","timestamp":"2026-04-29T16:35:15Z","committer":{"name":"Morten Svanaes","email":"msvanaes@dhis2.org"}},"workflow_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/workflows/10954","repository":{"id":66940520,"node_id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnk2Njk0MDUyMA==","owner":{"login":"dhis2","id":1089987,"node_id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjEwODk5ODc=","avatar_url":"https://avat